<br>
Back to the topic, I think your main problem with this mob is lack of resistances.<br>
<br>
As far as pushing Gulor, of course you push more with a shield equipped instead of your 2h, you are hitting it more. Pushing isn't how hard you hit, its how much.<br>
<br>
Kleg, that's cool. It is a skill, and I'm impressed you keep it up(this isn't sarcasm), however I have to disagree that everyone should keep it up to be a good warrior. A successful shield bash does not always interrupt a spell, just like it doesn't always stun. It's just like kick, it doesn't always get the job done. Faced with 2 ways where both might not get the job done, I will take the one that allows me to do more damage.<br>
<br>
An average equipped and decently (60%) hasted level 50 warrior will do 40dps or so. Switching out gear to ghetto bash, no matter how fast you can do it, eats into your damage output. Enough people switching out gear to ghetto bash, and you are taking a decent chunk out of your damage potential. Dead fast is less damage dealt to you too.<br>
<br>
Azn, I have my hotkey bank pretty full. 5 pages full. flipping through several pages to find the hotkey while the mob is pushed so you see &quot;you can not hit them from here&quot; filling your chat box isn't too good. It slows you down. The less there is to go wrong, the better. The simplest thing is to push, and kick, instead of ghetto bashing.<br>
<br>
Edit: Sandin,  i don't think it is stupid to not understand why we think its a little..off...to ask warriors to bash if we aren't fatties. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucrist0.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crist0</A> at: 1/18/02 11:07:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ugulorgularin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gulor Gularin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/18/02 11:07:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=825.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;it's not my job to bash&quot;</span><hr size=1> Using a shield definitely drops your damage output....thats why it is only really usefull on complete healing mobs or gaters.. the extra damage you do with 2 weapons is rendered useless if the critter rips off a heal on itself or gates out of your reach. I would never advocate warriors using shields in cases where speed of damage output is critical. <br>
<br>
As far as pushback goes...it happens when I bash..not when I smack it with my 1-HS. Although its true the 2-H weapons are slower and exert less pressure over time..there is an immediate pushback effect from a bash that I have only seen duplicated by a few of my stun type spells. I have noticed this with my warrior toon as well..not just my pally.<br>
<br>
I have to admit I was unfamiliar with the begging technique of increasing agro...I guess I need to put some work into that skill now as well. You learn something new here every day. <p>Gulor Gularin
