<br>
I don't completely agree with this statement.  I can switch in a shield and back to a sword in less than 1/2 second.  The chances that the offhand weapon is between attacks is high, so I wouldn't expect the damage output to decrease noticeably.  If I'm using 2 different weapon types or weapons with the exact same delay, it's even easier to tell when the right time to bash is by watching the messages.  Of course, if it takes you a while to swap in a shield, then yes, you'll see your dps drop.<br>
<br>
I do agree however, that it is most useful on the healing and gating mobs.  I was hoping to point out some of the other lesser known uses of this skill. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucsdmmnt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CSDMMNT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/18/02 11:47:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=825.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;it's not my job to bash&quot;</span><hr size=1> Not all bards swap instruments.<br>
