<br>
Anyway, if you have to rely strictly on having warriors bash to prevent gaters...it might be best to revise your playbook as there are more effect practices. There is nothing wrong with being adaptable to situations of course, but its best to assume that most warriors will not bash.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukleg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kleg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/02 4:54:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=825.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/Kleg.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;it's not my job to bash&quot;</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> There is nothing wrong with being adaptable to situations of course, but its best to assume that most warriors will not bash.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
